net.sf.mmm.util.query.api.argument

Interface Argument<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the generic type of the value to check by the Expression to build.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbstractArgument<V>, AbstractBooleanArgument, AbstractCollectionArgument<V,E>, AbstractComparableArgument<V>, AbstractEntityBeanArgument<V>, AbstractListArgument<E>, AbstractMapArgument<K,V>, AbstractNumberArgument<V>, AbstractSetArgument<E>, AbstractStringArgument, BooleanArgument, BooleanPath, CollectionArgument<V,E>, CollectionPath<V,E>, ComparableArgument<V>, ComparablePath<V>, EntityBeanArgument<V>, EntityBeanPath<V>, ListArgument<E>, ListPath<E>, MapArgument<K,V>, MapPath<K,V>, NumberArgument<V>, NumberPath<V>, Path<V>, SetArgument<E>, SetPath<E>, StringArgument, StringPath
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanPathImpl, CollectionPathImpl, ComparablePathImpl, ConstantArgument, ConstantBooleanArgument, ConstantCollectionArgument, ConstantComparableArgument, ConstantEntityBeanArgument, ConstantListArgument, ConstantMapArgument, ConstantNumberArgument, ConstantSetArgument, ConstantStringArgument, EntityBeanPathImpl, ListPathImpl, MapPathImpl, NumberPathImpl, PathImpl, SetPathImpl, StringPathImpl

    public interface Argument<V>
    This is the interface for a builder of an Expression checking one argument or comparing two arguments.
    Since:
    8.0.0
    Author:
    hohwille
    See Also:
    Args, Path
